Samson Folarin There is gridlock at the long bridge, Warewa section of the Lagos-Ibadan Expressway. The PUNCH gathered that the standstill was caused by a fire outbreak. It was learnt a car was gutted by fire in the middle of the bridge around 1.30pm. The car owner was said to be going to Arepo area of Ogun State when she noticed fire from the bonnet of her car. As soon as she hurried out of the vehicle, it went up in flames.